I"4<ol>
  <li>Place flour and salt and pepper in a shallow dish. Lightly coat steak in seasoned flour.</li>
  <li>Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook steak in small batches, adding more oil as required, for 2 to 3 minutes or until browned. Transfer to slow cooker.</li>
  <li>Combine all the other ingredients in a slow cooker, cover dish and cook for 4 hours or until steak is tender. Season with salt and pepper.</li>
  <li>Place pasta in shallow serving bowls. Spoon over casserole. Top with sour cream and parsley. Serve.</li>
</ol>
